Global Funds Buy Net 32.9 Billion Rupees of India Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-03-03T03:41:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/global-funds-buy-net-32-9-billion-rupees-of-india-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 32.9
billion rupees ($732 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
March 1, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 6.2 percent to 869 billion rupees, or 36.4
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign investors bought a net 4.2 billion rupees of shares
in the  cash  segment on March 1, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
